<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
"WHAT?"<BR>I ask as if enraged.<BR>"You are telling me porkrinds have gone up to 4 silver for a pound?"<P>The halfling merchant rolls her eyes. She knows full well I do not care about the price of rinds. Sometimes she appears to enjoy my eccentricities but today she seems less patient. "Mr. Callanish, if big fancy adventurers like you would stop brining in treasure by the wagonload we would not have all this inflation."<P>Suddenly the game of haggeling becomes less interesting to me. That telepathic bond between guildmembers is tugging at my consciousness. <P>How strange. Even when getting messages from Hate or Fear they have always been crystal clear. If I have missed them, it has been due to my own distractions. This message however is vague and distorted. It is from Scalpel, that much I can feel. It is a call for help. I feel that in the emotion of the message more than a clear picture of his words.<P>The halfing merchant asks if I am alright and I hear concern in her voice but my attention is rivited to this vaguge communication from my close friend and guildmate.<BR>I mutter something assuring her that I am alright an move to a more secluded location.<BR>Cloaking myself in anonymity to avoid the many requests my druidic spells and level of skill often attract, I concentrate on that guildbond that allows us to devine the location of fellow members.<P>The picture I recieve is of a lovely place, soft and green yet alien. The name that comes with it is cryptic to me. Grodawn. This place I have never heard of.<P>I project my thoughts to all available guildmates. "Scalpel is calling for help but I am having trouble locating him. This is a call to arms. Get his location if you can and let me know if you need to be picked up somewhere. We may well be on an impromtu raid here. And does anyone know where the hell Grodawn is?"<P>While waiting for responses I begin learning my travel spells and bookmarking my combat spells for a quick change.  <P>
<br>
<br>
