Nutryneaux reclined languidly on the curve of a grassy hillside as the sun made its journey into the horizon. Soft new blades of verdant grass laid beneath her supple form like a plush carpet and she relished the feel of it against her arms and fingers.  A sudden clank of metal nearby roused her from her half-slumber. Opening her eyes, she was met by a floating weapon and shield above her head. <P>"Meme?" the endearment came from none other but her son as he knelt beside her, his voice seemingly strained and urgent.<P>"What is it, mon fille?" Nutry resounded fondly and smiled warmly up at the flaxen haired young elf.<P>"I *feel* that something has happened..." Xenshen began his face contorted as if searching for the proper words. "Someone from the guild is in great danger."  He was a psion, gifted with the talents of the mind,a manipulator of thought, an enchanter of cognition. <P>Nutryneaux's face grew sullen and she sat up quickly placing her diminutive hands on his arms. She searched her son's face. "Xenshen, who is in danger?"  Some where in a the back of her thoughts, she was greatly relieved it wasn't Pyrus or Xenshen would have said so. Still the ominous tone in her son's voice was alarming. She squeezed his hands gently in hers as she watched him grapple with the warnings he was receiving in his mind. <P>Nutryneaux stood and wiped blades of grass from her leathers, then gently touched her son's cheek. "Thank you, mon fille. Have no fear, I will go immediately to the guildhall and see what there is to know."<P>The trees in the valley were awash with bountiful succulent new leaves. The child of the green jogged in between the myriad of trunks and disappeared into the threshold making her way to the guildhall.<P>------------------<BR>   <IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/siihouette/nutry23.jpg">   <p><FONT COLOR="#3299CC" SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[Edited 1 time by Nutryneaux LunaNuit on 20 April 2001 at 17:29]</font> 
