"Pick Max up in the circle at Misty." I hear at least that much of Gort's call. Still distorted and vague but unmistakable in its intent this time. There was more but I could not catch it nor waste time on it at the moment.<P>I slap my book closed and head to the nearby tunnel that bores through the hills and leads to Misty Thickett. It would have taken me longer to learn the teleport than to run there considering my proximity to the standing circle of stones.<P>On the way, there is barely time to consider how Gort came by this information. If the fuzzy comunicae he sent is any indication, my guess would be that he is now where Scalpel was when he called for help.<P>Reaching the circle of stones I see Max. He is crying and looks freightened, yet it is more the kind of fear I have seen in the faces of people in battle than on children filled with terror. <P>The last thing to do here would be to yell for Max to tell me anything. Whatever it was in his head that caused him to be so silent would clamp down like a trap if he was put under any pressure to speak at this point. I waste a precious second just staring at him patiently. <P>His trembling hand comes up. There is a curious little fetish in it shaped like a green dragon. I reach out to take it. It, ever so slowly, begins to turn its head in my direction. "Not yet" I say quietly to myself as I toss it into one of my pockets. There is a strong feeling in this item and I believe I have found the way to wherever Scalpel, and probably Gort, are.<P>My thoughts go out to the guildmembers as strongly as I can project them to gain attention.<BR>"EVERYONE AVAILABLE... MEET AT THE DEN NOW"
