<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
"Aren't you done yet?" I silently ask Kirico as I impatiently sit in the town market.  Marshalling the discipline learned over many years I calm my thoughts and attempt to become one with nature.<P>I feel the grass beneath me and ease into the flow of the life forces that surround all.  Slowly I feel my reserves of the arcane fill to their full potential.<P>"Only a moment more, love," comes the reply.  "She was in a particularly foul mood and I had to play her a tune before she would make it for me."<P>On the whole towns don't appeal to me- too much destruction and no regard for the life that already exists where the people want to dig.  As towns go, though, Rivervale isn't as bad as many.  The halflings that are the primary inhabitants seem to care for nature more than most.<P>"Excuse me, miss, but are you going to be teleporting to the commonlands soon?"  I look up to see a huge barbarian warrior standing in front of me.  Sigh, I could have sworn that I was being inconspicuous in this corner.<P>"I'm sorry, but I am waiting on a friend and then we are going to the Toxulla Forest.  Tis only noon, Kithicor Forrest should be safe if you hurry."  He mutters his thanks as he takes his leave.  Soon I see him talking to another across the market.  Brother, what some people will do to avoid a little walk.<P>I feel my mind relax as I hear Kirico approaching.  Always singing some sort of song he is just a joy to be around.<P>"Ok, I have the Jumjum," he says once he is by my side,"next on the list is Erud's Tonic."<P>"Toxulla Forrest is the closest I get to Erudin," I remind him.  I am just about to start the incantation when I hear faintly "pick up Max in Misty at the circle".  It is Gort, a good friend and high priest.  But what is he doing with Max?  I can't recall a time when I have seen Max and Scalpel hasn't been there.  I look at Kirico and see that he also heard the message.<P>"Come on, we aren't far from there," he said taking out his drum.  "It will only take a few minutes."<P>I nod quickly and stand.  A quick mental search and I verify that I have my greatest healing power available to command.  Kirico starts tapping his drum and I feel my blood start to rush through my veins.  My feet are light as a feather and I feel that I can outrace the fastest demon.  Kirico runs for the edge of town and I follow close at his heels.  I pay close attention as more than once I have missed a turn and crashed into a wall at this great speed.<P>Within moments we racing out of the town and heading for the circle of stones that serves as the entry point for those druids powerful enough to open the correct portals.<P>We come upon the standing stones poking up out of the mist from which this area draws its name.  As we approach I hear strong and clear "EVERYONE AVAILABLE, MEET AT THE DEN NOW".  It is McDuffy our venerable leader.<P>We come to the crest and see McDuffy standing next Max.  Max is trembling and McDuffy is trying to calm him.  Kirico stops singing and we slow down so as not to startle Max even more.<P>"What has happened?" Kirico asks when we are within speaking distance.  McDuffy looks up.  He is about as tall as the nine year old boy, but his face shows that he is no yearling.<P>"It isn't very clear," McDuffy begins,"it seems that Scalpel and Gort are in trouble.  Max managed to get away.  I believe that it has something to do with this charm."  The guildleader reaches into his pocket and pulls out a curious little totem in the shape of a green dragon.<P>I can feel the power in it as I gaze upon it.  It is alive!  I reach for it while McDuffy and Kirico say something that I cannot understand.  I take it from McDuffy's hand and feel the power pulsing in it- it envelopes me.  Kirico is shouting and from a distance I feel a pain in my hand, but it is too late.  The world disolves and I am no longer in the Misty Thicket.
