Posted 20 April 2001 22:00 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;



&nbsp;
 &nbsp; &nbsp;
<a href="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/cgi-bin/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=17&t=000018&reply_num=000007&u="><img src="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/NonCGI/edit_ubb6.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Post"></a>
 &nbsp;<a href="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/cgi-bin/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=17&t=000018&replyto=000007"><img src="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/NonCGI/quote_ubb6.gif" border="0" alt="Reply With Quote"></a>&nbsp;
   &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;       
 | <a href="javascript:ce_enforce('17','000018','000007');">Problem??</a>
  </FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I pause as I see the expression on Kizzie's face.  Obviously, she has not had a good day.  I get out my lute and I play the Carillion that I learned so many years ago.  Her face softens as she hears the music.  Always a crowd pleaser, that little ditty.<P>"Ah, then it is you again, Kirico" she says breaking into a smile. "Can I interest you in a ..., no there is only one thing that ye buy from me.  I'll lay you odds that you want some more Jumjum."<P>"Right as always, Kizzie." I carefully move up to the counter.  Though I am not a large person, the shops and houses were all built by halflings.  I feel like I should walk around on my knees to get the proper perspective sometimes. Carefully, I remove the three honeycomb from my backpack and lay them on the counter.  Reaching into my money pouch I grab a fistful of gold.  Counting carefully, I lay out 30 of the gold coins.  "Here you go,"<P>Deftly, she scoops the honeycombs into one drawer and the gold into another.  It is amazing to watch because she only uses one quick swipe of her small hand.<P>"Aren't you done yet?" I hear a voice in my head from my love, Jaia.  She gets irritable if we spend to long in town and we are rapidly approaching her tolerance.<P>"Only a moment more, love," I reply. "She was in a particularly foul mood and I had to play her a tune before she would make it for me."<P>I wait patiently while Kizzie goes into the back of the shop and fishes around for the proper item.  Finally, she comes back with the sealed jar of Jumjum.  A few more moments of small talk and I am headed out the door with my prize humming the tune that helps those of the arcane arts focus their meditations.  Fishing out the shopping list I cross off Jumjum and read the next item- Erud's Tonic.  Oof, it is a good thing that Jaia is humoring me with all of her "nature's gates" as she likes to call them.<P>I watch with some amusement as the barbarian warrior bows and takes his leave from her.  As she didn't even bother to stand he must have been asking to teleport to some far away place.<P>Ok, I have the Jumjum, next on the list is Erud's Tonic."<P>"Toxulla Forrest is the closest I get to Erudin," she says.  That isn't too far and I am about to comment on that when all of a sudden I hear a quiet voice say, "pick up Max in Misty at the circle."  It takes me a moment, but I recognize Gort's voice.  With just a hint of strain in it I know that it must be serious.  I have seen the wise holy man face down things that would make the most courageous warrior tremble with fear with nothing but a lackadaisical "Hey der, what have we here?"<P>"Come on, we aren't far from there," I say taking out my drum. "It will only take a few minutes".  Jaia nods and stands up as I begin tapping lightly on my drum.  The ancient melody making my blood course through my veins, my feet so light that they seem to not even touch the ground.  I run in the direction of the Misty Thicket.<P>It seems to take mere moments to get to the edge of town and enter the thicket.  I slow slightly and change course as the path to the druid's circle is one I know well.  As I spy the stones in the distance I hear "EVERYONE AVAILABLE, MEET AT THE DEN NOW". It is  McDuffy, leader of the guild and a halfling worthy of much respect.  I come to the top of the hill that hosts the standing stones as if a crown upon the land.  I see our leader standing with Max.  From this distance if I didn't know better I might be tempted to think that Max was the elder, although closer scrutiny would soon show the error.<P>I stop playing my drum and we slow down.  Often, people are unnerved by my swift approaches and Max looks to be agitated.<P>"What has happened?" I ask when we are within speaking distance.<P>"It isn't very clear," McDuffy says, looking up at me,"it seems that Scalpel and Gort are in trouble. Max managed to get away. I believe that it has something to do with this charm."  McDuffy reaches into his pocket and pulls out a tiny figurine.  It is of a green dragon with opal eyes.  I bend down to examine it.  The opals glitter, seemingly with a life of their own.<P>"What is that?" I ask turning to him.<P>"I don't know," he replies,"Max had it.  I can only assume that it is what trapped Scalpel and Gort.  It has great power, I can sense it."<P>"What do you.." I begin, then trail off.  Jaia has picked up the green dragon.<P>"Jaia NO!" McDuffy shouts.<P>A strange green nimbus begins to form around Jaia.  Quickly I slap the figurine out of her hand and try to grab her.  I feel the dragon as I knock it to the ground.  My hand passed right through her.  With a soft pop of inrushing air she is gone.  I stare at the space that had so recently been occupied by my love.  Turning, I see McDuffy carefully wrapping the green dragon in cloth before stowing it back in his pouch.  Max looks on with eyes as big as saucers.<P>"I have called everyone to the Den," McDuffy says sharply, "we must organize a rescue party before anyone else gets drawn in."  He pauses, then finishes quietly, "even you, Kir."<P><BR>
<br>
