<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
     "Lissssten to rootsss. Let water ssshape. Grow old. Ssstrong."<P>     These were the predominant thoghts, each a year in the making, in the mind of the elemental. It fell and rose in the crust of the earth like some sluggish raft in a sea of mud.<P>     Suddenly, its rudimentary mind was probed and commanded to obey. Reluctantly at first, but then with growing speed lent to it by the magic, it oozed to the surface, ready to do the bidding of its new master.<P>     "Yessss Masssster." It said slowly.<P>     "Protect the boy." The figure holding the radiating gem said. <P>     A mental picture of "the boy" flew into its mind and the elemental searched for its new master. He found him close at hand, and glided to his side. "Massster ssayss protect boy. One...two...massstersss......protecting." It sensed the dragon by that time, but as it was not yet harming the boy, it remaind protective.<P>     Then, as abruptly as he was summoned, the elemental felt the original magic that had compelled him to be brought to this plane stop. He was not sure what to do. It looked back to its summoner and saw him lying on the ground, the dragon close at hand.<P>     "Massster gone." It said, but then it turned back to the boy. "Mussst ssstay to protect new massster." It reasoned. <P>     It then felt another presence close at hand, and saw a small humanoid come toward the boy. Apprehensively, it moved closer. Then, pop! The boy was now gone!<P>     "One massster....two massssterss....no masssterss...one....two....too MANY!"<P>     White-hot rage began to fill its small brain, and it began to convulse. Sheets of rock began to crack and pop on its surface as its muscles bulged to incredible size. It doubled, then trebbled its bulk, and the dull slate eyes turned a malevolent firey-red.<P>     "Musssst kill!!!" It roared, and searched the area for foes.<P>     Just then, it saw the beautiful druid pop into the clearing and begin to deftly prepare her spells.<P>
