<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Kirico had been correct those times he told me what a good combination a druid and a bard could be. Between my teleportation to the circle of commons and his drums we were arriving at the Emerald Tiger's Den so quickly that very few of our members had yet arrived. Fortunately, a few bleary eyed ones appeared to have been eithier drinking or sleeping here already. Others, like Nutryneaux, had heard the call and had the means to arrive swiftly.<P>A lot of questions are asked all at once. It appeared that most of them had heard the same calls as we did so they had some idea what was going on. Signaling for silence I shout. "Suffice it to say Kirico and I have found a way to where Gort, Scalpel, and now Jaia are." <P>Turning to Blixa I give her instructions. "Blix, get Max to a room upstairs and send someone you trust up to stay with him. Maybe call in a favor from one of those paladins that wander down from their guild to flirt with you all the time."<P>Seeing that we are in a hurry Blixa assigns this task to a young, and rather startled looking member of the Northern Paladins who had been watching our entire exchange with fascination over his mug of ale. I raise my bushy eyebrows as I see how quickly he snaps his attention to the task then turn my gaze back to Blixa questioningly.<P>She looks both a little embarrassed and impatient as she tells me, "Never mind that you nosey old halfling, stick to your business." I hear as well as feel that several more members have arrived during our exchange.<P>"Alright." I say, "All guildmembers gather round. Those of great and small skill alike. We have no idea what we face here but everyone will be useful. Pretend we are doing one mass group teleport." <P>I look in Blixa's eyes with an intensity I save for when I need for people to know I am in earnest. "Blixa. Take that Pike from over the mirror behind the bar. Stand as far from me as you can. I am going to be holding a small dragon statue. It will begin to move. Very soon after that I, and hopefully all those touching me, will fade from this place. As that happens Knock it from my hand with the pike."<P>A few questions arise but I wave them to silence. "Kirico and I have seen this done. Trust us." I turn again to Blixa, "Any who are left behind, in the chance that it will not take us all in one trip, or any who come after us, should repeat this procedure. You stay behind to direct this my friend. Leave the dragon fetish where it lies until the next group is ready to go. Once it is touched, the process begins."<P>I feel the hands reach out and touch me. Small ones, large strong ones, gentle<BR>ones, "wow" I think "that one must belong to Rockabilly or Palant". The fetish is in my hand. It turns to look at me. I feel it knocked from my grasp as.....<P>We arrive in pandemonium. It is soft green country but I hardly notice. In a glance I take in Gort, Jaia, a Dragon and a rogue Earth elemental<p><FONT COLOR="#3299CC" SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[Edited 1 time by Mcduffy on 21 April 2001 at 07:40]</font> 
