<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<I>Much faster this way,</I> Nutryneaux, a Child of the Green, thought. Tired of having to enter the town by negotiating through the sewer systems like a common criminal, Nutryneaux took the direct route. <P>"Your foul deeds have earned my contempt!" The illreputed militia guard shouted as he spewed out further insults and called for more men. Fortunately the lackey's sword missed her as she ran by him at the gate. Nutryneaux took in a scoffing breath and smirked at him. It never ceased to amaze this elfess how one's reputation in cities traveled faster than a bard with battle drums!<P>Still blessed with an accelerated animal spirit in her stride, she ran deftly around the maze of walls into the northern part of city while the militia men fell behind. The northern guards, in league with the paladins of light, smiled warmly with respect to her when she arrived. The militia men never followed that far into the city but stayed in their corner of the dismal world of stone and mortar they had taken over. Nutryneaux mused as she ran through the streets towards the guildhall. If not under such a time constraint, she would have stood at the zone and shouted back to the militia guards on the other side just exactly what she thought them! <P><I>Foul deeds? I'll show you foul deeds!</I>, she thought with a wry smile, not sure what she would have shown them though. However, the Child of the Green had seen many humans using such taunts on one another and would know how to decipher the meaning even if she didn't.  <P>***<P>Nutryneaux finally arrived at the guildhall Den, and felt utterly relieved to have done so unscathed. Once inside, the perisistant tone of doom was palpable and she glanced around cautiously.  Kirico and McDuffy arrived shortly after, and the hall erupted into questions and concerns regarding the mage Scalpel and his son, the druidess Jaia, and the cleric Gort.<P>"Suffice it to say Kirico and I have found a way to where Gort, Scalpel, and now Jaia are." McDuffy shouted above the commotion and had Blixa escort a young lad, Scalpel's son, upstairs.<P>Nutryneaux regards the guild leader curiously, her mind in a flurry of thoughts as he quickly explained the dimensional door he intended to use to tranport willing guild members to where Scalpel, Jaia, and Gort had disappeared.<P>McDuffy looked about to the group as he held up a small dragon statue,  "Kirico and I have seen this done. Trust us." <P>A distortion like a vortex of transparent liquid swirled around the halfling's fingertips where he gripped the statue. Nutryneaux blinked as the flux of air began growing and encircled McDuffy, Kirico,  and the others in his direct vicinity. Like an arch made of gelatin, it appeard as shimmering cystalline gateway and the group shifted through it. The Child of the Green leapt to her feet and dove into the fluctuating air, her fingers clutched around someone's arm.<P>The emerald hued walls and the tiger carpeted den gave way to green country side in another place far away from the city. Taken aback and heightened to this strange new locale, Nutryneaux,  felt the need to review her list of incantations. Then she heard it, the distinct sounds of leathery wings moving through the air. Dragon!<P><B>BAM!</B> A rock hard fist hit her square in center of her back nearly knocking the breath out of her. Nutryneaux stumbled to her knees, as the second blow missed over her head. Wincing in pain she turned her gaze and saw a rogue earth elemental rearing back for another swing...<P><P>------------------<BR> <IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/siihouette/nutry23.jpg"> 
