"A plat short and a day late, the story of my life" Vandril said as he felt the movement of the guild. Being a wizard is different than most other magic using beings. Druids feel the way that Norath trembles when thier magic is used. Wizards feel the very essence of magic move. Great battles and massive spells feel like hammers ringing in his head. The benefit was, he knew where they went.<P>Quickly grabbing his spell book, he sat for a few seconds, memmorizing several of his teleport spells. "I may not be a bard or a druid, but I am quick enough". A moment later the world rushed around him and to those that watched, he simply disappeared. A soft pop was heard where the air rushed in to fill the void where he once stood.<P>The sounds of the dragon was the first thing to assualt his senses, the next was the rogue earth elemental as it threw itself at him. Fortunately it wasn't powerful enough to break through his shield instantly. Grinning as he cast he watched his magic surround the elemental's body and then turn into a thick wall. It always ammused him to paralyze a earth elemental.<P>The grin was quickly wiped away as the dragon's talons ripped through his weakened shield and blood came out his mouth. Crying outloud, shouting at the top of his lungs he unleased with the mightiest spell he knew. The dragon scream in pain momentarily as the massive sphere of ice and cold ripped into its body. <P>As the ice fell away from its body, Vandril turned to run, terrified. The damage was minimal, only patches of scales were missing and the dragon seemed only barely hurt, worse it seemed even angrier.<P>"well back to the old drill" he said to himself. "Hopefully people will live to rez me" Running as fast as he can trying to take the dragon away from his companions, giving them a chance to act unified.<P><BR>
