Nutry flies across my vision as she is blind sided by the rogue elemental. Expecting a palnar battle I had memorized my strongest exile spell. A quick incantation and a large ammount of earth slides off the rockish body of the summoned creature. It turns its featureless form in my direction but is quickly distracted by a mighty blow from the sword of Raiachu.<P>I glance at the dragon and see that it has gained most of the groups attention. My healing power does not begin to rival that of Gort but it is enough to sustain Rai while he finishes off our earthen opponent. Those things hit hard once they go feral.<P>Once it has fallen my attention turns to our more serious opponent. To my relief someone has managed a successful snare on the dragon. Gomb is standing ready to go toe to toe with the beast. It will not be enough. Gort's complete healing will be needed there along with any of our spells that can get through its inate magic resistance. <P>It is still mass confusion. We have had no chance to group up. It has been arrive and fight. I cannot even tell who all is present. <P>Calling forth Wings of Death I send swarms of bees, flies, misquitoes and a few insects that must be unique to this pace to worry at the eyes and wounds of the great reptile beast. Kirico's tunes ring out. Not even being certain what they are doing, they always fill my heart with hope and raise my spirits. I just begin to think we have this under control, then my eyes go to the horizon and my heart sinks.<P>"If anyone gets a free moment try to contact Scalpel's spirit." I yell. "Get permission to move his corpse away from the battle. Then, as soon as possible, rez him and start him recouperating. We are going to need him."<BR><p><FONT COLOR="#3299CC" SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[Edited 1 time by Mcduffy on 22 April 2001 at 13:01]</font> 
