Running as fast as he can Vandril is running around in a wide circle, not to far from help but far enough the dragon won't worry about the others. Ignoring the fact that he is nearly dead, his lung punctured from that last lucky swipe the wizard runs on.<P>I feel the power, great healing magics being wrot on the field, not Gort but someone almost as good. Looking around trying to see what my friends are up to, I feel the touch of serenity... that brief moment when all is right and you are in complete balance with nature... and damn! its not hard to breathe anymore!. Scouring about my mismashed friends I see that Amethyste, bless her heart is here and she brought that troll too. Good, good.... time to make her earn her keep.<P>"She's all yours Gomb!!" Vandril shouts, twisting with agility that is uncommon in a wizard, he stops turns around and looks right at the Dragon. The dragon senses victory and closes in for the kill,Only to strike thin air. What was to be a quick kill before killing that druid that undid all his work, turned to be an even more infuriating defeat. Howling in anger the dragon whirls around to look for Amethyste, that wizard got away because of her, only to have the light obscured by millions of insects and vermin from Mcduffy's spell.<P>"Over here you overgrown Gecko!!, yeah you flower smelling iguana!" Vandril shouted from behind Gomb to the dragon. He had shadow stepped away from the dragon to disorient it, and to bring it to the one who was tough enough to go toe to toe with it. "It's not much my friend but it should add to Amethyste's magic" Vandril whispered to Gomb as he casted his next spell. The thorns that grew out of Gomb's skin now had a strange redish glow. If someone had the time to actually examine it, they would have seen that there were thousands of little fire elementals dancing on the barbs.<P>Rearing to the insults, the dragon looked for where they came from and saw Gomb standing in all her might, braced for the charge.  Trolls may not taste good but they keep well...<P><p><FONT COLOR="#3299CC" SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[Edited 1 time by Vandril on 22 April 2001 at 14:03]</font> 
