Swirling mist and then it clears.  My stomach gives a lurch then settles- wow that was a trip.  Not the usual sensation I have from teleporting.<P>I look around at the pandemonioum.  I recognize the wolf that is Jaia.  Thankfully, she is safe for the moment at least.  I see the dragon attacking Vandril and Gomb running over to take care of it.  Raichu is also moving in.<P>Gort is over by Scalpel's body, but is watching the combat.  I begin mixing my songs so that the maximum effect will cover my friends.  Fire and Cold resistance, Magic resistance, and damage shield all intertwine in the melodies that I sing.  I keep time with my drum and the magic that is imbued in it boosts the effects to a useful level.<P>"Completely healing Gomb," Gort announces as he stands and begins the slow ritual.<P>I grunt in pain as an incandescent shower of green sparks surrounds me and my compatriots.  The damage shield goes down and I feel my muscles cramp briefly.  That could have been much worse I think as I look to see if anyone has fallen.<P>"Train of .... Bentoveroids.... coming from the north." McDuffy shouts.  I turn and see a pack of the brutes heading for our little party.<P>"Jaia," I call out, "please fill me with the Spirit of the Wolf."  I sit down and get out my song book.  Several years ago I learned a little ditty that might help in this situation.  McDuffy looks at me strangely, but Jaia doesn't even blink.  Within moments I feel the strength come into my legs.  Having reminded myself of the tune I stand and switch to my horn.  <P>Running toward the incoming group I test out the composition.  It sounds a little harsh to me, but judging by the reaction of the bentoveroids it is having the proper effect.  They scream and cover their ears.  As a group they try to seek out the source of their pain.  All to soon they have a bead on me and run straight for me.  As they get closer I can see the blood streaming from their ears.  Everybody is a critic I laugh as I start to back up.  I run faster as they get closer- staying just out of their reach.<P>"I have these occupied for the moment," I call out.  "Vandril, when you get a chance- do you have Bonds of Force ready?"<P>Ouch! I pick up the speed a little as one of the critters reaches me with one of their long arms.  This is going to take awhile.<P>
