<FONT SIZE="1" color="#3299CC" face="Verdana, Arial">
Posted 26 April 2001 12:16 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 &nbsp;<a href="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/cgi-bin/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_profile&u=00000109" target=_blank><img src="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/NonCGI/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Profile for Scalpel Spelsmith "></a>&nbsp;
 &nbsp;<a href="http://none" target=_new><img src="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/NonCGI/homepage.gif" border="0" alt="Author's Homepage"></a>&nbsp;
&nbsp;
 &nbsp;<a href="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/cgi-bin/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=private_message&u=00000109"><img src="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/NonCGI/priv_message.gif" border='0' alt="Send New Private Message"></a>&nbsp;
 &nbsp; &nbsp;
<a href="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/cgi-bin/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=17&t=000018&reply_num=000024&u=00000109"><img src="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/NonCGI/edit_ubb6.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Post"></a>
 &nbsp;<a href="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/cgi-bin/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=17&t=000018&replyto=000024"><img src="http://www.wrathofdragonclaw.org/NonCGI/quote_ubb6.gif" border="0" alt="Reply With Quote"></a>&nbsp;
   &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;       
 | <a href="javascript:ce_enforce('17','000018','000024');">Problem??</a>
  </FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
     I glide acroos the cool stone path faster even than when I have been blessed with the Spirit of the Wolf from my druid brothers and sisters. Mists swirl about my legs and the sky is gray and overcast. Although the scenery seems muted and drained of color, it is a comforting, restful place - very restful.<P>     I approach a low stone wall with mistly shapes verily swimming in the ether on the other side. Several seem to notice my approach and come towards me, beckoning for me to cross the wall and to take my place with them. The urge is near irresistable.<P>     I waiver, thinking of my dearest friends, brothers and sisters all, pitched in a dreadful battle, to which I have brought them. I resist the call of the mists - but it is not enough. Slowly I move to the wall.<P>     Suddenly I hear the voice of Mcduffy, chanting softly. He speaks of fresh earth, rainfall, warm sun, new buds on trees, and flowers coming to life. He speaks of snowy winter nights with your toes next to a warm hearth, the taste of a mug full of hot spiced cider, tall tales shared among friends and laughter. He speaks of true friendship and love. He reminds me of the joy I have in my son. <P>     That one is enough!<P>     Slowly, I open my eyes and try to sit up. PAIN! <P>     The wounds on my back and on my chest are all ready clotted and begining to heal. I touch my head and wince; That one may leave a scar I muse. I then scan the sceen.<P>     A lump forms in my throat as I see how many of my sisters and brothers have come to my aid. I have come to question many decisions in my life but never this one - I have choosen guilds well indeed! I almost forget what is going on as I watch the heroics of stout Gomb, going toe-to-toe with the great dragon and the play of scintillating magics in the air around the battle. Brave Gort, bruised and bloody, is by my side. Looking puzzled, he rises to his feat to cast healing magic my way.<P>      Perhaps it is the song of Kirico that fills my heart with hope, but strength seems to be returning to my body as I rise. "Save it for those who need it my friend. I have full mana, and that's all I need." I have been pulled from the brink once today and if it is my lot to return, so be it!<P>     I take in a fresh breath of air. It is a good day to die!<P>     I look to the rest of the battle, and would have doubled over in laughter, would my body have allowed it. That old campaigner Motrin is sitting astride what seems to be left of my earth elemental giving it a stern lecture! How odd though, although the elemental seems almost destroyed, it is huge! I send my thoughts to it and reestablish my control.<P>     "Massster!" It says. Although this is directed to me, I notice with some amuzement it is still gazing Motrin's way.<P>     " I am healing you." I think to it. "Will you obey in this fight?"<P>     "Yessss my Massster." It complies.<P>     "Agronomus, Aidi ton filis" I shout, and, considering our situation, add, "Berserkus liberatus!" I briefly wonder if I have the power to control such a being, but quickly banish those doubts, and flash a mental image of myself as powerful and confident to the elemental. It rises from the ground and glides toward the dragon. "Is Motrin going to ride that thing like a horse into battle I wonder?"<P>     Looking elsewhere, I notice Kirico's beloved, Jaia, is in battle with several ape-shapped creatures. "Where in all the nine hells did these come from?" I muse. Knowing that these creatures could pitch the battle, disrupting casters from their important task at hand, I send a message to my son, and find, with great relief that he is safe in the Den.<P>     "Son, if there if there are any fighters with you, they are needed here in the battle. Have them come quickly, but you stay there!"<P>     I then turn my attention back to the battle at hand and blanch...the dragon has reared back and is taking in a great gulp of air!<P>     <p><FONT COLOR="#3299CC" SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[Edited 1 time by Scalpel Spelsmith on 26 April 2001 at 17:55]</font> 
