<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Nutryneaux rose from her knees and took a narrowed glance at the elemental who had socked her. It was aimless and mistook her for an enemy, as summoned creatures do when they have lost their masters. However, many incoming guildmates handled the poor hapless creature subduing it for the time being. <I>Was that Motrin straddling it? </I>she curiously mused to herself.<P>Wiping the dirt and grass from her hands and leathers, she readied her thoughts for the battles that quickly ensued. A swing of leathery wings followed by trunk sized talons which rumbled the horizon as Raichu and Gomb began deflecting it. Nutryneaux's eyes widened, having never faced dragons this close before. Her mind began reeling, <I>What should I do?</I> <P>Her  first thoughts coalesced, and she quickly turned her focus onto Raichu and then on Gomb as sprigs of pithy barbed vines jutted from their bodies like amour made of thorny protection. She tried to rise vines from the earth beneath the dragon's talons, to stop it or slow it, but her efforts were lost in futilty as the dragon was just too strong.<P>Nutryneaux blinked hard, as Jaia's words broke through the commotion, "I have to go give Kirico a hand with the bentoveroids. I will be back as soon as I can. Amethyste you and Nutryneaux are the only backup healers- McDuffy is meditating."<P>Swallowing hard, and shoring up her reserves Nutryneaux shouted, "I am ready!" From her pack she flipped the Mace of Tunare into her delicate pale hand, and in the foreign landscape it shown like a sunlight dancing through an emerald shaft, filling her thoughts with the added strength and mana she needed for what was to come.<BR><P>------------------<BR> <IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/siihouette/nutry23.jpg"> 
