"Train of .... Bentoveroids.... coming from the north."  Mcduffy shouts. Great.. just great I think to myself. Time to shine.  Sitting quickly down I open my book to the back, usually not a good sign because that is where my fiercest spells are. Well i have spells that do more damage outright, these are spells of mass destruction.<P>Standing I look at Amethyste and before I can even utter the words I feel the spirit of the wolf strength my legs. "thanks" I say grinning. I love having good friends.<P>Kirico's call to me "Vandril, when you get a chance- do you have Bonds of Force ready?" breaks my momentary lapse. Laughing I call out "That's like asking if Jaia is with you!!" as I run to chase him. Looking for the angle I run to cut him off and as he brings those things closer to me, I begin my chant.<P>I open my eyes and see Kirico outdistancing them nicely now. The spectral shackles binding the Bentoveroids, slowing their charge enough that they realize they can't catch the guard and that I was the cause of this.<P>Just like giants I think. Barely speaking I begin my next spell, I have the time before they get to me. The thunderclap that ensued was louder than the Dragon, and the Bendoveroids looked stunned. Their flesh had been ripped apart by the sheer volume of the thunderclap but they were still standing. "so you want more eh?" They are going to start calling me a druid with all this thunder and lightning soon I think to myself as I start the next chant.  The rest of the Bentoveroids fall in the lightning storm that hit. They were just recovering from the shock of my last spell. "Bentoveroids are Burtoveroids now"<P>I look back at the main fight, the Dragon doesn't look please that her minions have become one with the soil, but she has Raichu and Gomb to deal with.  I know it will only be a matter of time before she takes offense to Gort and his healing abilities. Time to distract the dragon again.<P>
