  </FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
It is a warm summer day as I lay about the warm fields of Commons.  I merrily help the younger adventures with the nasty creatures that they do battle with. Hardening of skin here, increase in health regeneration there, all to pass the time. As I just get done helping a young monk with a puma, I get a mental summons by my older brother Mcduffy asking for help.  Great I think to myself, whats he gotten himself into now.<P>I imbue myself with the speed of a wolf and race off to the Tigers Den. As I approach the gates of West Freeport I see Sir Lucan standing there, berating his men. Oh if there was more time, I would have some fun but alas duty calls. <P>He happens to see me as I race by and starts to bark orders to his men to have them stop me.  Not now Lucan, but maybe later,  as I race for North Freeport.<P>I enter the Tigers Den and see Blixa standing there. Knowing my brother, he would entrust her with any crucial information as to his where abouts.  Hey Blixa, where is the old coot? I ask.<P>She tosses me a Dragon totem and says, Use this to get with him, others are already there. Scalpel seems to be in trouble.<P>I can sense the fear in her voice.  Oh joy, I think to myself, another merry time to be had by me.<P>I focus on my brother with the totem in hand and I feel myself start to get light headed as I am being transported to another plane.  Just before I am fully immersed in the fog, I release the totem and let it fall to the ground in the Tigers Den. <P>When I come back from the haziness, I am standing in a grassland that stretches as far as the eye can see.  I am slowed by the teleport, the fog slowly leaving my mind. I look around see my friends from the Alliance of the Griffin.  They seem to be fighting a big green thing. My vision is still blurry but is focusing fast.<P>A DRAGON!!!!!!<P>Well thats just great. Of all the things that I need to be dealing with right now. <P>I look around to take an assesment of the area and situation. Gomb and Raichu are fighting the Dragon. Gort, Amethyste, Nutryneaux, and Mcduffy (old coot) seem to be backing them up with Vandril, Kirico, and Jaia laying waste to god knows what the hell those things are.  I spy Scalpel and Motrin playing with an earth elemental, is Motrin trying to ride that thing?<P>Well it looks like its time to make my presence felt.<P>I open my spell book and start to memorized some spells that will make this dragon think twice before messing with my friends again.<P>I stand up and target the Dragon just as I see it start a huge intake of breath.  I call upon my god Karana to grant me the spells and power to help us in the battle that we now face. <P>I call upon the wind to momentarily stun the beast, NO DRAGON BREATH FOR YOU! With it stunned, it no longer is able to breath on us.<P>Not wanting to waste time, I mutter some arcane symbols and encase the Dragon in ice. Watching its skin crack, I immediately begin casting again.  Now its skin begins to melt as fire rages around it, as it screams in pain, I make a hasty retreat knowing full well that it will now want to try and find out who was causing it so much pain.<P>WELL HELLO THERE YOU UGLY, GREEN, OVERGROWN IGAUNA, COME AND GET SOME!<P>That should let everyone know that I am here I think to myself. If you want to make an entrance, might as well do it in style.<BR>
