Finally getting some sleep after days of waiting for Hadden to come give me my earring back.  I'm awoken by a shoven from Blixa.  "Scalpel needs help, use this to get there", she says. <P>"Oh, TUNARE!  Am I ever going to get some damn sleep.", I grumble as I roll out of the down bed.  I rub the sleep out of my eyes and think to myself..."Sleeping on the ground is all fine and good, but I'll still take a down matress any day."  <P>I slowly Picture in my head the image given to me from the stone figurine.  Gathering the forces of nature in my surrounding area, I release them in a quick pop.  I'm near instantly transported halfway across the world.  Having arrived, take quick stock of my surroundings and begin a small spell that will allow me to fly, then a spell that will speed my journey.  I head out towards the sounds of battle. <P>"A very tired and worn out Comblast reporting in" I shout out.  I sit down for a few moments trying to gather more energy.  I see the Dragon off in the distance.  I feel bad  that there is really nothing I can do at the moment.  Until I have some energy built up I would just be dragon fodder.
