Braganz haad been concentrating fiercely on his lock picking skill in the East parts of Freeport when he received the call. It must have been several call before it finally got through, because the Den was empty when he finally did arrive.<P>Appearing in a strange land, he immediately hid himself from view and took stock of the situation. Scalpel was on his feet again, and the dragin still looked as though it hadn't been harmed all that much. The extra creatures seemed to be well in hand with Kirico, Jaia and Vandril, so Braganz did his best to sneak behind the behemoth of a lizard.<P>Carefully avoiding swishing tail as he approached the dragonf rom behind, Braganz selected his biggest pointiest weapon from his arsenal and took careful aim at the back of the dragon, just above the tail, hoping for a good hit. The hit was good! And it seemed Raichu and Gomb had been doing a very good job of taunting the dragon, as it barely even flinched at the attack from behind.<P>With that in mind, Braganz didn't waste time evading the combat at all, and simply started swinging until he could find another good oppurtunity to place his Chokodai Prod in the back of the dragon again. Of course he was very noticable behind the dragon, agily (though barely in some instances) avoiding the tale of the dragon still, and he felt his speed increase as Motrin imbued him increased speed and strength.<P>The smile on Braganz's face could be seem easily to all who cared to look at him. It had been some time since he had seen any combat action, and he was enjoying it immensely. He vowed to spend less time in town now that he'd had a chance to work on some of him more "socially unacceptable" skills.
