<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Mala...resist...mala...resist...mala...RESIST!<P>Scalpel was running out of options and his friends were getting hurt! He had all ready tried the old faithful; Shock of Swords, and when it had done nothing more than jar a scale loose, he knew the beast had a great deal of magic resistance. The rogue elemental was at least doing some damage, but it still was not enough. He could only hope that he might be able to lower the dragon's magic resistance to help the other casters before he died, but time was running out, and so was his mana.<P>"OOM!" Shouted Mcduffy, and Scalpel verily cringed. Well, Scalpel thought, might as well go out in a blaze of glory.<P>Scalpel thumbed through his worn tome with practiced fingers, back to the pages he almost never used...Ah! Here it is - Scinitllation, this may give him some heartburn anyway!<P>Scalpel began to ready the spell, but stopped abruptly when he saw the now familiar green vortex begin to form nearby. To his dismay, no mighty warrior stepped through the arch, but only a small boy. "Son! What are you doing here..go back!"<P>Scalpel saw his son run to him. Max had never disobyed him before, in fact, Scalpel had sometimes wished he would if only to see a change in him, but this was not the time!<P>Max came to his father. He gazed into Scalpel's eyes, then briefly touched his hand.<P>"Son, no! You have no idea..." But then Scalpel stopped short...Max had dropped his hand and was casting! <P>Small purple rings began to spread out from Max and head to the dragon. The rings pulsed with energy as they encircled it, then gave a loud "Pop!" and disappeared. <P>Scalpel gaped in astonishment. "Ummm...dragon Malaed!" he shouted. He then looked in wonderment to his son, who was all ready casting again.<P>Corruscating blue sparks began to emmanate from his son. The magic covered the small boy from head to toe, seeming to draw force from him. Then, with another pop, they flew from him and fell on a shower to the party. Scalpel felt the mana in him renewed...fully!<P>Scalpel turned his attention back to the fight, and saw Mcduffy look to him, puzzled.<P>"Hit it hard now!" Scalpel yelled. His jubilation would have been short-lived, however, if he would have looked to see his son, paler than ever, collapse to the ground.<P><p><FONT COLOR="#3299CC" SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[Edited 1 time by Scalpel Spelsmith on 26 May 2001 at 10:51]</font> 
