<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
"Dragon Malaed" I hear Scalpel shout.  That is good news. It will be so much easier to get spells through now.  Jaia and I come over the rise after taking out the remaining overoids and survey the scene.<P>Gomb and Raichu are hacking away from the front.  I spy Braganz burying his weapon into the back.  Gort is meditating out of reach- standing occasionally to heal the tired fighters.  Omcduffy has joined the fray, calling upon Nature's fury to help strike down the beast.  Amethyste is trying another snare as the one by Jaia fades into memory.<P>Scalpel is casting... no wait, that isn't Scalpel casting.  It is Max.  What in the name of all that is holy is Max doing here?  I see a shower of blue sparks spread from Max in a familiar pattern.  Jaia stiffens.<P>"Full mana," she reports.  I see Scalpel swing into action summoning god knows what horrific effect to aid in the battle.  Max crumples and falls.<P>"You help with the fight," I tell Jaia, "I'll take care of the kid."  She nods, attention already focused on the fighters to see if any spot healing is needed.<P>Quickly, I run to Max and pick him up.  He is very pale and hardly breathing.  Quickly I start the Hymn of Restoration to aid his healing.  A little Jig of Vigor mixed in also seems to help.  Reflecting on the blue sparks that I had seen coming from him I add that song prized by all casters-  the chorus of clarity that sharpens minds and enables the mystic forces to flow without the natural resistance of man.  Repeatedly, I sing these to him as I try to pull him back from the brink of the abyss.  Craddling him in my arms I carefully move him off to one side- out of the direct line of any dragon breath.<P>I look up to see how the fight is going...<p><FONT COLOR="#3299CC" SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[Edited 1 time by Kirico on 27 May 2001 at 01:21]</font> 
