(posted by Shilok)<P>Shilok awoke with a start.  Strange dream she'd been having.  She<BR>could only remember snatches of it now... a wild light, a clutter <BR>of voices in her head, and her father's voice above all.<BR>She searched for his voice now, but Mcduffy was somehow out of her <BR>reach.  Shilok did not wonder at this for long, as her thoughts were <BR>interrupted by a door opening and small feet scuttling across the floor <BR>to her bed.  In the candlelight of her room at the Emerald Tiger's Den, she<BR>could barely make out the figure of Max.<BR>She sighed easily.  The little boy always made her feel somehow peaceful,<BR>and his quiet was often a welcome change from the boisterous older<BR>members of the guild.<BR>Max himself did not seem peaceful now, though.  He remained silent, but <BR>Shilok could tell there was something urgent at hand.  Quietly, without<BR>question, she slipped off her bed to stand in front of the boy.<BR>"Tell me what to do," she whispered, for she would obey any command.<BR>She knew something of the boy's secret... enough to know that she would<BR>follow his lead even if it meant defying his father Scalpel and her own<BR>father, Mcduffy.<BR>Max softly took her hand in his and led her to a balcony overlooking the<BR>tiger-carpeted den.  Slowly, he pointed at the barmaid, Blixa.  As he did,<BR> Shilok noticed something small in his hand glinting in the light.<BR>She understood.  She was to distract Blixa, possibly even keep her from<BR>sending word to the others.  They were in danger, wherever they were, and<BR>only Max could help them.  Shilok alone understood this, and she nodded<BR>gravely to the little boy, now frail and small in the light of the great<BR>hall.<BR>"Go," she whispered.  "I will cover for you as long as I can."<BR>And with that, Max stepped back into the shadow of her room and with a <BR>blinding flash and a quiet *pop* he was gone.<BR>Shilok prayed for the safety of the guild, whatever great battle they<BR>might be in.<BR>But now she turned her sights on Blixa and the few others gathered in the hall.<BR>She hoped she could distract them long enough for Max to return safely.
