While the bentoveroids were an easy mark, they still drined Vandril's most precious resource, his mana. Thinking he still had some left in him, Vandril began his short lived but massive unslaught of fiery destruction. Five and then a sixth torrent of fire engulfed the dragon.<P>Unlike most casters Wizards imbue each of thier spells to rend through a creatures magic resistance, must like an arrow finds the soft spot in a suit of armor. It works better when the dragon has been tash'd or malao'd but at least he could hurt it. Not enough though seeing that the flames had only barely damaged the critter.<P>As Vandril appraised the damage, the tell tale pulple rings with the splash of green encircled the dragon. A grin broke his face and just as quickly disappeared.  Finally mala went through, but no mater, by the time I am ready for another assualt, Gomb and Raichuy will be dead.<P>Blue filled Vandril's vision. Magic was exploding all around him, engulfing his being for what seemed like hours, but was only a few short seconds. The need to rest was gone. "Wow, did you learn a new chant Kirico?!?!" Vandril shouted.<P>Renewed and regenerated, Vandril was ready to begin anew when the dragon reared back. Even in midspell Vandril knew this would not be good, dragon breath is ugly, destroying even the mightiest fellows in a single blast. Good thing troll flesh just doesn't do anything but sag. The deafening roar that echoed through out the land, was enough to break Vandril's concnetration on the spell. <P>Must leave, must run, must..... No I will not run.. Dragon Fear, in my past battles I ran like orcs run from me now, but experience has taught me. With eyes still closed, I pray for a split second that I am not the only one who resisted.<P>For the dragon breath is surely next.<BR>
